Class ZipEntry

java.lang.Object
  com.mot.iden.zip.ZipEntry

public class ZipEntry
extends java.lang.Object

This class is used to represent a ZIP file entry.

setCrc

public void setCrc(long crc)
Sets the CRC-32 checksum of the uncompressed entry data.

Example: 
 CRC32 crc32 = new CRC32();
 zipentry.setCrc(crc32.getValue());
It sets the CRC-32 value. This isn't strictly nessary for deflated entries, but is doesn't hurt.

Parameters:
crc - the CRC-32 value
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the specified CRC-32 value is less than 0 or greater than 0xFFFFFFFF
See Also:
setCrc(long)
